cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses modified backpropagation methods for explaining deep neural network predictions, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves analyzing the performance of these methods on image data, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of the modified BP methods, which is related to optimization and numerical analysis, indicating cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category.
